This paper is about a new model for group mobility in wireless networks, which is relevant to the field of computer networks and communication. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a new set of intrinsic properties for a mobility model, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance evaluation of networking protocols and resource allocation algorithms, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also uses discrete event simulators, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the characteristics of future generation mobile wireless networks, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
